<title>USA: Comcast wins option to acquire control of E! - WSJ.</title>
<headline>Comcast wins option to acquire control of E! - WSJ.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-01-10</dateline>
<text>
<p>Comcast Corp won the option to acquire Time Warner's 58 percent stake in E! Entertainment Television for about $310 million, The Wall Street Journal reported Friday, citing sources familiar with the situation.</p>
<p>The story said Time Warner's partners, including Comcast, recently triggered a buy-sell provision tied to a December deadline in the original partnership accord.</p>
<p>The story said Comcast emerged with the unilateral option to buy Time Warner's stake, sell to Time Warner through proxy the other 42 percent or possibly leave ownership as is.</p>
